                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d614">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">856d.6363/565</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Tobin</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-03-27">March 27,
                            1929</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 650</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to the Department’s instruction
                    No. 645 of March 14, 1929,<note n="7" xml:id="d614fn7">Not printed.</note> with
                    regard to the interest which Mr. Francis B. Loomis of the. Standard Oil of
                    California, had expressed to the Department in obtaining oil concessions in the
                    Netherland Indies, Mr. Loomis has advised the Department that he will shortly
                    proceed to Holland where he will endeavor to obtain for his Company a concession
                    or concessions. You will please render Mr. Loomis such assistance as you may
                    deem appropriate.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State:<lb/>
                    <signed>W. R. <hi rend="smallcaps">Castle, Jr.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
